        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 25 at 4:56PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 455 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from near Ballston Spa to Niskayuna to near Voorheesville.
Movement was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and brief, heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Albany, Schenectady, Troy, Clifton Park, Rotterdam, Saratoga Springs,
Cohoes, Watervliet, Rensselaer, Colonie, Scotia, Mechanicville,
Delmar, Latham, Guilderland, Niskayuna, Ballston Spa, Menands,
Voorheesville, and Green Island.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 90 between exits 8 and 25.
Interstate 890 between exits 4c and 9.
Interstate 87 between exits 23 and 7, and between exits 8A and 13N.
Interstate 787 between exits 1 and 9.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
